Gauteng has the highest number of new coronavirus cases. Gauteng Executive committee is expected to brief the media today, on how it will enforce measures to manage the spread of Coronavirus in the province. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng premier David Makhura and the members of the provincial executive will hold a media briefing on the province's plan to curb the spread of the coronavirus. This comes after a special provincial leadership meeting that was held on Tuesday. There have been 116 COVID-19 cases in South Africa so far. Gauteng has the highest number of new coronavirus cases. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? So far South Africa has no reported any death from the coronavirus which has claimed the lives of nearly 8,000 people worldwide. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.